cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SE

This paper discusses the integration of non-volatile memory (NVM) with Java runtime, which involves system software stack and programming models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with the design and implementation of distributed systems. The paper also proposes a new abstraction for persistent programming, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the recoverable mechanism for crash consistency, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and operating systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
